01:56:12.204 --> 01:56:15.192
I don't have any around. Usually, I have like two or three laying around.

01:56:15.193 --> 01:56:20.771
I like drinking stuff. It's like you got the tea. I told you, it's like Texas—we drink a lot of tea.

01:56:20.772 --> 01:56:26.184
I love McAlister's tea. And I can go in there and get a big jug of that, unsweet.

01:56:26.185 --> 01:56:32.098
We won't drink the sweet anymore because it's making me blow up. I don't want to get fat.

01:56:32.099 --> 01:56:40.819
It took me a while to get used to drinking unsweet tea, but for a while, with the ice, I said, "Just add a lemon to it, Di.

01:56:40.820 --> 01:56:48.211
I can't take this."Sweet is too sweet. It tastes like syrup because most people put too much, I think.

01:56:48.212 --> 01:56:57.264
Well, that lady said they put like four huge bags of sugar in a five-gallon thing.

01:56:57.265 --> 01:57:03.460
And I'm like, "That's like diabetes in a jug."I'm not doing that. I didn't realize it.

01:57:03.461 --> 01:57:06.319
And we were drinking a lot of those sweet gallons because Megan liked it, you know.

01:57:06.320 --> 01:57:18.516
And I said, "Well, it's not good for your teeth anyway because of all that sugar on those teeth, and I don't want cavities."So, I thought, "Well, why not just do the unsweet tea, and we'll try it."And now I'm getting used to it. It took me a little bit.

01:57:18.517 --> 01:57:33.879
It's the same thing when you get a sweet tooth like I've had, and you get in there and you snack on things, and then Diana finds those all-natural chips and she says, "This is natural."And I think, "Oh, it's natural; it's good for me."No, it ain't good for you, Brandon.

01:57:33.880 --> 01:57:38.259
You don't need a bag of chips. No, I like those. Those are natural.

01:57:38.260 --> 01:57:45.258
They're okay. They're friendly. But now she's on the kick of making bread.

01:57:45.259 --> 01:57:50.959
And she found—okay, so listen to this, this is awesome, y'all.

01:57:50.960 --> 01:58:02.002
She got these wheat berries from Billy Burke. His wife sent them to us and she said, "I want to bless you.

01:58:02.003 --> 01:58:08.196
I want to teach you how to make this bread."I love Billy Burke. He is my friend.

01:58:08.197 --> 01:58:11.631
And now he's my double friend because he taught us how to make muffins.

01:58:11.632 --> 01:58:18.176
And she makes these muffins that are homemade, freshly milled.

01:58:18.177 --> 01:58:23.759
She has a miller and she grinds up the wheat in there, and she gets the real berries and she grinds them up.

01:58:23.760 --> 01:58:35.323
And Dina, she goes, "Honey, what kind do you want? Ezekiel bread tonight."And there's all kinds of old grains—spelt—that are really good.

01:58:35.324 --> 01:58:44.635
It starts with a K; I can't remember the other one. And so she makes these hot muffins and I'm telling you what, they're a blessing.

01:58:44.636 --> 01:58:55.439
I told her, "Okay, I'll do one or two a day."But they really are good for you because they scrub your colon walls. So, they're helping you.

01:58:55.440 --> 01:59:10.325
They're supposed to—now, it's like real fiber, you know, and so she's doing all this research stuff, finding out about the vitamins and stuff that's in real wheat, and how the processed flour is not as good for you.

01:59:10.326 --> 01:59:15.995
So, it's really cool. And I'm like, "Hey, you know, the history of it."We perish for a lack of knowledge.

01:59:15.997 --> 01:59:21.256
And I told her, "The more we learn, the more we learn. Isn't this wonderful?

01:59:21.257 --> 01:59:28.056
Isn't Jesus wonderful?"Hot muffins, hot muffins, woo! With a little butter on there.

01:59:28.057 --> 01:59:39.839
I said, "Thank you, baby."I said, "Diana, I need a hot muffin with a little blueberry in there."I don't know, I just try to be real with y'all, you know? We're just real, y'all.

01:59:39.840 --> 01:59:51.899
I get so—don't you get so tired of all the celebrity stuff where you can't just be real with people and just talk and be fun, where everybody's so out there?

01:59:51.900 --> 02:00:01.315
But I realize the more people get kind of weird with you, and you got people that are kind of flaky and they try to stalk you and be weird, but we're just human.

02:00:01.316 --> 02:00:10.109
We're just real. I don't like all the celebrity Christian stuff.

02:00:10.110 --> 02:00:20.598
We all put our pants on one leg at a time. We all go to the bathroom. We all stink and get BO. And not one of us can say we don't. No.

02:00:20.599 --> 02:00:29.234
So, I don't care who you are that thinks you're so such-and-such, that's got a big old head walking in a room and going, "Well, I got it all going on."No, you don't.

02:00:29.235 --> 02:00:33.399
You got issues and you're hiding them. And I'm just being real with y'all.

02:00:33.400 --> 02:00:42.301
You need Jesus just like I need Jesus. And the only one that is perfect is him. And we're all going from glory to glory.

02:00:42.302 --> 02:00:48.617
And everybody has something they're going through, so stop trying to be something that you're not.

02:00:48.618 --> 02:00:56.718
Just be like Jesus as best you can. And we're all going to try—we'll all probably mess up, but we try.

02:00:56.719 --> 02:01:04.773
You know, I try. We ain't perfect. But I'm going to tell you all, the Lord wants us to do what we're doing and I'll do it.

02:01:04.774 --> 02:01:19.194
I just say, "Okay, God."You know, weight things, exercise—nobody wants to exercise, but I do it. I try. I told my flesh, "Shut up, flesh!

02:01:19.195 --> 02:01:29.114
Get on that bike, ride, go out there, push the mower, do something, stop being lazy."All right, I've talked too much.

02:01:29.115 --> 02:01:35.759
I'm going to get myself in trouble. No, it's good, I like it. Well, I think they need to hear it.

02:01:35.760 --> 02:01:38.519
Sometimes it's good to hear it. They're saying they like sourdough.

02:01:38.520 --> 02:01:44.797
I want to try sourdough. I want to do it. Sourdough, uh-huh. That's my goal, to get there.

02:01:44.798 --> 02:01:50.760
Sourdough is good. You haven't made that for me, but I've had it some other places.

02:01:50.761 --> 02:01:57.395
"I'm a noob, I'm learning."What's my favorite? It starts with a Kam—what is it?

02:01:57.396 --> 02:02:03.969
Kamut. No, not kombucha. I like kombucha, too. You like kombucha, do you all?

02:02:03.970 --> 02:02:14.765
The Lord spoke to me—I was praying about kombucha and the fermented, the growing the mushrooms on top, you know, that fungus, and you ferment tea with it.

02:02:14.766 --> 02:02:28.728
And he started talking to me about kefir. And I was drinking the kefir and eating the grains because of—for your stomach, and for your bowels, and for your immune system, for probiotics.

02:02:28.729 --> 02:02:33.740
And the Lord talks to me. So, I drink a lot of kefir, and I know it's fattening.

02:02:33.741 --> 02:02:45.384
Kamut, Kamut, that's the wheat. But I make homemade kefir, and strain it, and sometimes it's real tart.

02:02:45.385 --> 02:02:53.033
But I'll eat the grains off of there and it's like a treat. It's kind of like yogurt, and I mix it with my yogurt and stuff, but it's full of probiotics and stuff.

02:02:53.034 --> 02:03:01.835
So, we're learning about that. There was a lady on YouTube that was talking about it, and that's where I—because I was praying in the spirit, and the Lord gives me these things.

02:03:01.836 --> 02:03:05.837
It's kind of like this. I'll let you in on another something.

02:03:05.838 --> 02:03:13.407
I was praying about a berry, and the Lord said it was the size of your thumb and it was a goji berry.

02:03:13.408 --> 02:03:19.952
The Lord said, "Pray about the goji berry,"and I saw Mount Fuji.

02:03:19.953 --> 02:03:28.319
And I saw this berry, and the Lord said, "Pray over this."I don't know, but when He talks about it and He tells me, I'll eat a couple of them.

02:03:28.320 --> 02:03:40.799
I'm like, "Well, I know there's something about this."I don't know what the goji berry does, but He tries to tell you about things that have been here forever, that are really good for you, from what I understand.

02:03:40.800 --> 02:03:47.512
So, I just pray over it. I'm like, "Well, that's interesting."I just get these little cues from the Holy Spirit, and you just keep going with it.

02:03:47.513 --> 02:03:53.913
That's why I talk about kefir and kombucha and—what's that brand?

02:03:53.914 --> 02:04:01.118
I drink the strawberry. I like that strawberry. Yeah, the grass-fed—no, kombucha.

02:04:01.119 --> 02:04:07.074
Oh, it's the strawberries. Yeah, it's strawberry. I think that's what it is.

02:04:07.075 --> 02:04:15.329
Isn't that what it's called? Well, I don't know. It's whatever it is. It's this little cup of a little bottle; it's glass.

02:04:15.330 --> 02:04:21.433
It comes from California, but I think you've drunk it on here before, haven't you?

02:04:21.434 --> 02:04:26.207
I probably have, but I try just to drink water, and it blends in with my green screen.

02:04:26.208 --> 02:04:30.898
It's transparent, yeah, with my—are we still with the American flag?

02:04:30.899 --> 02:04:39.678
This one? Yeah. What is it? Synergy, GT. Yep. I don't think it's called Synergy; I think it's just GT.

02:04:39.679 --> 02:04:51.198
Yeah, it's not a plug. We're not plugging it. No, we're not telling you to buy it. They're not giving me a kickback; I'm just talking.

02:04:51.199 --> 02:05:12.748
So, people need to know that I do not—listen, I've had huge companies offer me big bucks to do commercials on here and wanting me to do stuff, and I say, "No, no, we've dedicated this to Jesus, and that's strictly what—you cannot buy the anointing.

02:05:12.749 --> 02:05:21.227
You'll not merchandise it."And whatever ads YouTube puts up there, this is their platform, but I will not do it.

02:05:21.228 --> 02:05:27.719
And I believe this is important that you all understand: we do not merchandise the anointing.

02:05:27.720 --> 02:05:35.064
It is something—it's not mine. I'm a steward, and I refuse to be this way.

02:05:35.065 --> 02:05:51.279
And I don't care if you offer me $100,000 a year or not. No. Your flesh screams, and I say, "No, shut up. Not doing it. No. This is precious.

02:05:51.280 --> 02:06:01.137
This time with you is precious, and we're thankful for every single one of you that show up and want to pray with me every day."It's been amazing what God's done.

02:06:01.138 --> 02:06:06.584
China's up to 22,000 people now. Yeah, I just uploaded their video for today.

02:06:06.585 --> 02:06:13.087
You did? Yeah. I love the Asian people. I love them; they're precious.

02:06:13.088 --> 02:06:25.975
You know, God has given me such a heart for the Asians, praying for them, and for revival for their nation, all around over there, for the Philippines, all around. I'm just believing God for something big for them.

02:06:25.976 --> 02:06:37.568
The Lord said, "I have not forgotten you."And I'm telling you all, my Japan channel still struggles, the Philippines channel struggles some, but Vietnam's kind of taking off, and South Korea exploded.

02:06:37.569 --> 02:06:47.244
It's growing huge, and so is my Hispanic channel and my Portuguese.

02:06:47.245 --> 02:06:52.197
Yeah, Portuguese. So, glory to God for all those folks that pray with us.

02:06:52.198 --> 02:06:58.573
So, all right. Well, thank you for joining us today. Yes, we appreciate every single one of you.

02:06:58.574 --> 02:07:06.726
We truly do. Thank you for showing kindness to us. You know, there's—I know everybody has an opinion, and I'm not here to always play a victim.

02:07:06.727 --> 02:07:09.625
I appreciate people defending me in the comments and stuff.

02:07:09.626 --> 02:07:14.975
Folks, I'm telling you, you'll be persecuted for the Word's sake. I get it; it's part of the territory.

02:07:14.976 --> 02:07:27.016
But I want to tell you, every single one of you that love on my family, you send us cards of encouragement, blankets for my daughter, showing us things, you know, like the drone, everything—I just want to say thank you.

02:07:27.017 --> 02:07:34.074
You don't have to do that. But it's just showing the love of God, and sometimes I need it.

02:07:34.075 --> 02:07:52.590
There's days I'm down, and I go, "Man, Lord, I need a pick-me-up."And you get something in the mail, a letter or something, some sister saying, "Hey, I'm praying for you,"and I go, "Thank you."Just you praying for me means so much; it's just showing His love.

02:07:52.591 --> 02:07:58.045
We're finished; we're finishing our race strong in these last days and doing what God's called us to do.

02:07:58.046 --> 02:08:02.102
And I know this is just the beginning for what the Lord has told us to do.

02:08:02.103 --> 02:08:16.479
We have a lot to do, and a short time to do it. A long way to go and a short time to get there—Smokey and the Bandit.

02:08:16.480 --> 02:08:25.357
God bless you all. Well, remember—oh, subscribe. Have you subscribed today? Please subscribe.

02:08:25.358 --> 02:08:32.691
Click the notification bell, click the like button, comment something nice down below, and do all the things that you need to do.

02:08:32.692 --> 02:08:34.629
I appreciate it. We'll be back again tomorrow, and we'll pray.

02:08:34.630 --> 02:08:42.158
We've got to pray over Israel, and the Lord said mandate from January 14th to the 4th.

02:08:42.159 --> 02:08:46.683
So, and I know we've been on here way too long. So, God bless you all.

02:08:46.684 --> 02:08:52.956
Put a smile on your face and a song in your heart. Jesus loves you so much, and we love you.

02:08:52.957 --> 02:09:00.821
God bless you all, and we'll see you again soon. God bless you. Thank you. I'm so glad they came tonight. Bye-bye.

